ion":"1784265046901708001-642e8f8e-e188-496f-acd6-c3cce44807a6"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"6c75fc2760c3b2497cfb314275e59bbbf8c222381caae1632c70515c13838a22","event_uuid":"4fd072c8-339c-4bb8-a78b-f9481ddce579","position":{"commit_sha":"b4d6f97a56b03d2059b7ea56f84aeab42746123e","position":"1784265049515062001-4fd072c8-339c-4bb8-a78b-f9481ddce579"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[],"created_at":1784230959891368001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"bbe4c5fd-f8bc-42b8-879a-f8901c7ebf1b","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"}],"description":"# Ship a client-usable AGENTS.md template + a drift-guard test\n\n## Why\n\nTeams that ADOPT rebar in their own repos need to teach their agents how to drive rebar (the\nticket workflow, claim/gates, MCP tool set, idea/linking/tags/session-logs) WITHOUT inheriting\nrebar's internal dev specifics (Gerrit split-remote, module-size, Serena, our landing flow).\nBecause `AGENTS.md` is read by every major harness, one copyable, provider-neutral template\nserves all of an adopter's agents. A test keeps the template's rebar-usage content in sync with\nthe authoritative source, so it cannot silently drift.\n\n## What\n\nAdd `templates/AGENTS.md`: the portable \"how to drive rebar\" guidance sourced from the\nauthoritative rebar-usage content, with clearly-marked placeholders for the client's own\nbuild/test commands and landing flow. Add a drift-guard test that compares only the delimited\nrebar-usage region against its canonical source.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `templates/AGENTS.md`, one new test (e.g. `tests/unit/test_client_template_sync.py`), and a\ndocs-index reference. Out: scaffolding via `rebar init` (deferred — a shipped file was chosen).\n**Depends on S1** (already linked `depends_on`): the canonical portable rebar-usage content lands\nin `docs/ticket-model.md` (+ the workflow loop) first.\n\n## Design decisions (spike-validated)\n\nThe existing `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` compares WHOLE files byte-for-byte; that does\nnot fit the template, which is intentionally not byte-identical to any doc (it carries client\nplaceholders + different framing). Resolved: sync a DELIMITED REGION. Keep the canonical portable\nrebar-usage prose in one source; embed it in `templates/AGENTS.md` between\n`<!-- BEGIN rebar-usage (generated; do not edit) -->` / `<!-- END rebar-usage -->`; the test\nasserts that block is byte-identical to the canonical source (mirroring `_identical` + a\ndivergence self-check). Client placeholders live outside the delimited block.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `templates/AGENTS.md` exists, is provider-neutral, and contains no rebar-internal\n  Gerrit/module-size/Serena content.\n  - Proving: `test -f templates/AGENTS.md && [ \"$(rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena' templates/AGENTS.md)\" = 0 ]`\n- [ ] The portable rebar-usage content is a delimited region byte-identical to a single canonical\n  source.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'BEGIN rebar-usage' templates/AGENTS.md`\n- [ ] A drift-guard test compares ONLY the delimited region against the canonical source, fails on\n  divergence (proven by a self-test), and runs under `make test`.\n  - Proving: `make test`; perturbing the delimited block makes the test fail.\n- [ ] Client placeholders (build/test/landing) sit OUTSIDE the delimited block and carry no\n  rebar-internal content.\n  - Proving: reviewer confirms placeholders are outside the BEGIN/END markers.\n- [ ] The docs index references `templates/AGENTS.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'templates/AGENTS.md' docs/`","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"templates/AGENTS.md","reason":"client-usable template"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_client_template_sync.py","reason":"drift-guard test"},{"path":"docs/README.md","reason":"reference the template"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"],["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"642e8f8e-e188-496f-acd6-c3cce44807a6","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"064f-0484-2795-4ac7","ticket_type":"story","title":"Ship a client-usable AGENTS.md template + a drift-guard test","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["e30314b0-4808-48d4-9763-5004583865d4","bbe4c5fd-f8bc-42b8-879a-f8901c7ebf1b","5fd2610b-0f6d-48a7-8228-f82ab49489b0","ff51f1f1-5228-49cb-970d-54cd99df7134","c92dc55d-2487-463c-9e52-51b527912545","0d0ca8ac-8432-4266-bf82-30c4089d44fd","920f083e-a6f0-4c7d-ad99-4459c582e384","389e1245-5d86-4f27-973a-fc0817c9f00a","228185cf-c0f4-4a2d-a94c-5406886484fe","ff2d7a63-dce9-4b63-9e57-d2adfbcf65e4","d7575465-9406-4afb-a7a9-6b6b9b96b7de","16443449-3bf0-4a61-9fdc-0532594dfe4f","214caef9-864f-41ed-89c5-da4ec5cfb1b1","9fb81670-768c-44d9-9aad-0be4ea09efe0","1d95f46e-e7be-4406-8900-2c7c048356fc","642e8f8e-e188-496f-acd6-c3cce44807a6","4fd072c8-339c-4bb8-a78b-f9481ddce579"]},"env_id":"","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784346937209011001,"uuid":"6a6c9455-1fa7-4757-8897-20c1cbd56e5d"}